        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2019-03-08T01:41:37.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"150479\">\n<blockquote>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/wine.asp?iWine=1575378\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><strong>2011 Domaine Harmand-Geoffroy Gevrey-Chambertin 1er Cru Lavaux St. Jacques</strong></a> <em>- France, Burgundy, C\u00f4te de Nuits, Gevrey-Chambertin 1er Cru (3/5/2019)</em><br>\nThe nose is quite smoky, with some floral spice and red fruits thrown in for good measure. It is mid-weight, nicely balanced and has plenty of meat and earth savoury nuance. It is drinking nicely right now.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Posted from <a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">CellarTracker</a></em></p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Bertrand Dugat told me to check out their wines a few years ago, and I wasn\u2019t disappointed. Seems like they\u2019re on a very positive trajectory. Great holdings, too.</p>",
